sample.title: Why No Tax On Tips May Be Making America‚Äôs Tipping Problem Worse
sample.description:

Lawmakers pushed for the provision to increase take home pay for the nation‚Äôs tipped employees. Data suggests it‚Äôll boost average take home pay by $1,300 annually. However, some industry experts and tipped employees feel this provision has the potential to do more harm than good. They also suggest wage reform is the better way to go about helping low income tipped employees.

Thailand and Cambodia agree ceasefire after weeks of deadly clashes | BBC News
sample.description:
Thailand and Cambodia have agreed to an immediate ceasefire, the defence ministers of both countries have said in a joint statement.

The two sides have agreed to freeze the front lines where they are now and allow civilians living in border areas to return home, halting almost three¬†weeks of intense clashes in which dozens of people have been killed and nearly one million displaced.

The ceasefire took effect at noon local time (05:00 GMT) on Saturday. Once it has been in place for 72 hours, 18 Cambodian soldiers held by Thailand since July will be released, the statement said.

The breakthrough came after days of talks between the two countries, with diplomatic encouragement from China and the US.
